researchers

.

weekend

.

Several

is

.

Nevertheless
,

the
University	B	University of Pennsylvania	Q49117	ORGANIZATION
of	I	University of Pennsylvania	Q49117	ORGANIZATION
Pennsylvania	I	University of Pennsylvania	Q49117	ORGANIZATION
Medical
Centre
said

release
.

Muscular
dystrophy
is
a
fatal
illness
in
which
the
body
's
muscle
tissue
degenerates
and
is
replaced
by
fat
.

Death
strikes
in
early

.

Individuals
with
the
disease
have
a
non-working
version
of
a
gene
responsible
for
producing
a
crucial
muscle
protein
called
dystrophin
.

In
the
study
at
the
University
's
Institute	B	Institute for Human Gene Therapy	--NME--	ORGANIZATION
for	I	Institute for Human Gene Therapy	--NME--	ORGANIZATION
Human	I	Institute for Human Gene Therapy	--NME--	ORGANIZATION
Gene	I	Institute for Human Gene Therapy	--NME--	ORGANIZATION
Therapy	I	Institute for Human Gene Therapy	--NME--	ORGANIZATION
,
researchers
altered
a
common-cold
virus
to
carry
a
version
of
the
working
dystrophin
gene
.

The
virus
,
which
also
was
altered
to
minimise
its
susceptibility
to
the
immune
system
,
was
then
injected
into
the
muscle
cells
of
mice
bred
to
lack
dystrophin
genes
.

In
the
experiment
,
between
30
to
40
percent
of
the
muscle
fibers
in
one
group
of
mice
produced
dystrophin
for
two
weeks
before
diminishing
.

Similar
results
had
been
obtained
previously
in
test-tube
cell
cultures
,
but
not
in
live
animals
,
the
university
said
.

The
university
said
methods
are
still
needed
to
make
enough
of
the
altered
virus
to
treat
humans
,
to
further
decrease
the
immune-system
response
to
the
virus
,
and
to
deliver
the
virus
to
human
muscle
tissue
.
